args:
Vania continues to press the prince, explaining
that her entire clan has fallen into a slumber
that will only end if she becomes queen. She
reveals the loneliness she's felt, and the prince
suggests mingling with the local villagers.
Sooo, given any thought to becoming my\nbloodkin? About ready to get the chomp?
What?! No. I'm not so capricious as\nto have changed my mind overnight.
Booo. Fine. About how long will it take,\nthen?
I can see you're quite insistent about this,\nVania. Might I ask the reason?
Huh? Oh. It's 'cause I need to hurry\nup and become a proper queen.
Indeed. It has been decreed that my\nliege will ascend to the throne and\nreign as queen of the vampires.
And is creating bloodkin related to\nyour ascension?
A vampire's bloodkin are more than\nmere servants.
One's might as a vampire is directly tied\nto the strength of their progeny. It is a\nmatter of paramount importance.
Understood. Yet you're still a child, Vania.\nSurely you needn't be in such a rush to—
No I'm not, I'm BIG! You all are the kids,\ncompared to me.
What? Ah... I do recall hearing that\nvampires have lifespans that transcend\nthe limits of mortality.
So how old are we talking? Like, mom-\ntier? Grandma? TURBO GRANDMA?!
Way, way, WAY older!\nBack me up here, Malinda.
Indeed. A vast stretch of time has passed\nsince Vania was born unto the world.
And yet, it remains true that she is still a\nchild by vampire standards.
All right, then we're back to my original\nquestion. Why the hurry to form bloodkin?
I...I don't have any other choice.\nIt's that or be alone forever.
The vampire clan now finds itself\nlost in an unending slumber.
What brought such a thing on?
I don't know. I was conked out until just a\nlittle while ago, too. And I can't remember\nanything from before I went to sleep.
Wait, on top of all that, you've got\namnesia?! Girl, your life is a MESS!
I remember SOME things. Like that I had a\nlittle brother. That my best friend was a\ndragon... Malinda.
But it all feels like something from a\ndream now.
Have you no insights to offer, Malinda?
Alas, naught of detail. Nothing save for\nan ancient legend that tells of a queen's\nawakening rousing her clan from slumber.
Which means if I can just go all royal,\neverybody'll wake up.
And I've gotta hustle here, so...
If you're done with all the questions,\nlet's get you all on Team Vania already!
That's a lotta baggage for one bewinged\nlittle gal to be carrying around—and I\nwould know.
While I cannot become your bloodkin, I\nmay be able to help ease your loneliness.
Ready or not, here I cooome!
You're way too good at being ＂it,＂ Vania.\nThe round's over before it even starts!
Right?! And I'm a hide-and-seek pro—\nno, a hide-and-seek LEGEND!
Mwah ha haa. Sorry, but I'm a vampire.
Vampires possess far keener senses than\nmere mortals. Her advantage is significant.
Wow, vampires are awesome. But you're\nstill not gonna find me next time!
Challenge accepted.\nYou can try me anytime!
Thanks for keeping my children company\ntoday, Vania.
Oh, there you are, bloodkin.\nBabysitting isn't my favorite pastime,\nbut it wasn't all anguish and turmoil.
Ha ha. That would be more convincing if\nyou weren't grinning ear to ear the whole\ntime. Come, let's head back for now.
Okay. And, uh, by the way...
Er, no, it's just...\nNever mind. Forget it!
